<div class="non_toggle_area" id="comment-4129786">
  <div class="non_toggle_label">
       <span class="scomments_info">Thu, 11/07/2013 - 00:52 | <a href="/news/2013-11-06/why-bitcoin-surging#comment-4129786" class="active">4129786</a></span>
              <b><a href="/users/urban-roman" title="View user profile.">Urban Roman</a></b>
  </div>

  <div class="comment-content">
    <div class="author"><div class="picture">
  <a href="/users/urban-roman" title="View user profile."><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/pictures/picture-34256.jpg" alt="Urban Roman&#039;s picture" title="Urban Roman&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>The price is still increasing because of more people hearing about / discovering / getting interested in it.</p>
<p>I was pretty sure it had reached saturation at about $120 or so, earlier in the year, but it obviously has not. Every time a story breaks in the popular media (Silk Road Dude Arrested), more people hear about it, more people who are worried about the dollar and the destruction of their savings, and more people jump in. I got a few around $20, but continue to be amazed by the rate of ascent.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="links"><ul class="links"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul></div>
